label.value: Prostate Cancer cT2 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Prostate cancer confined within the prostate.  Tumor found in one or both lobes by needle biopsy, but not palpable or reliably visible by imaging, is classified as T1c. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Prostate Cancer cT2a TNM Finding v7

value.value: Prostate cancer with tumor involving one-half of one lobe or less. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Prostate Cancer cT2b TNM Finding v7

value.value: Prostate cancer with tumor involving more than one-half of one lobe, but not both lobes. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Prostate Cancer cT2c TNM Finding v7

value.value: Prostate cancer with tumor involving both lobes. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Prostate Cancer cT3 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Prostate cancer extending through the prostatic capsule.  Invasion into the prostatic apex or into (but not beyond) the prostatic capsule is classified not as T3 but as T2. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Prostate Cancer cT3a TNM Finding v7

value.value: Prostate cancer with extracapsular extension (unilateral or bilateral). (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Stage III Testicular Yolk Sac Tumor AJCC v6 and v7

value.value: Stage III includes: Any pT/TX, Any N, M1, SX.  M1: Distant metastasis. SX: Marker studies not available or not performed.  (AJCC 6th and 7th eds.)

label.value: Prostate Cancer cT3b TNM Finding v7

value.value: Prostate cancer invading seminal vesicle(s). (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Prostate Cancer cT4 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Prostate cancer with fixed tumor or tumor invading adjacent structures other than seminal vesicles such as external sphincter, rectum, bladder, levator muscles, and/or pelvic wall. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Prostate Cancer Clinical Regional Lymph Nodes TNM Finding v7

value.value: A clinical finding about one or more characteristics of prostate cancer, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system as they pertain to staging of regional lymph nodes.  (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Prostate Cancer cNX TNM Finding v7

value.value: Prostate cancer in which the regional lymph nodes cannot be assessed.  (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Prostate Cancer cN0 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Prostate cancer with no regional lymph node metastasis. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Prostate Cancer cN1 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Prostate cancer with metastasis in regional lymph node(s). (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Prostate Cancer Clinical Distant Metastasis TNM Finding v7

value.value: A clinical finding about one or more characteristics of prostate cancer, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system as they pertain to distant metastases.

label.value: Prostate Cancer cM0 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Prostate cancer without evidence of distant metastasis. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Prostate Cancer cM1 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Prostate cancer with distant metastasis. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Prostate Cancer cM1a TNM Finding v7

value.value: Prostate cancer with metastasis to non-regional lymph node(s). (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Acute Erythroid Leukemia

value.value: An acute myeloid leukemia characterized by a predominant immature erythroid population.  There are two subtypes recognized: erythroleukemia and pure erythroid leukemia. (WHO, 2001)

label.value: Prostate Cancer cM1b TNM Finding v7

value.value: Prostate cancer with metastasis to bone(s). (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Prostate Cancer cM1c TNM Finding v7

value.value: Prostate cancer with metastasis to other site(s) with or without bone disease. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Stage I Prostate Cancer AJCC v7

value.value: Stage I includes: (T1a-c, N0, M0, PSA less than 10, Gleason equal or less than 6); (T2a, N0, M0, PSA less than 10, Gleason equal or less than 6); (T1-2a, N0, M0, PSA X, Gleason X).  T1a: Tumor incidental histologic finding in 5% or less of tissue resected.  T1b: Tumor incidental histologic finding in more than 5% of tissue resected.  T1c: Tumor identified by needle biopsy (e.g., because of elevated PSA).  T2a: Tumor involves one-half of one lobe or less. cN0: No regional lymph node metastasis.  pN0: No positive regional nodes.  M0: No distant metastasis.  Gleason Equal or Less than 6: Well differentiated (slight anaplasia).  Gleason X: Gleason score cannot be processed.  (AJCC 7th ed.)

label.value: Stage II Prostate Cancer AJCC v7

value.value: Stage II includes: IIA (T1a-c, N0, M0, PSA less than 20, Gleason 7); (T1a-c, N0, M0, PSA equal or more than 10 and less than 20, Gleason equal or less than 6); (T2a, N0, M0, PSA less than 20, Gleason equal or less than 7); (T2b, N0, M0, PSA less than 20, Gleason equal or less than 7); (T2b, N0, M0, PSA X, Gleason X); IIB (T2c, N0, M0, Any PSA, Any Gleason); (T1-2, N0, M0, PSA equal or more than 20, Any Gleason); (T1-2, N0, M0, Any PSA, Gleason equal or more than 8).  T1a: Tumor incidental histologic finding in 5% or less of tissue resected.  T1b: Tumor incidental histologic finding in more than 5% of tissue resected.  T1c: Tumor identified by needle biopsy (e.g., because of elevated PSA).  T2a: Tumor involves one-half of one lobe or less.  T2b: Tumor involves more than one-half of one lobe, but not both lobes.  T2c: Tumor involves both lobes.  cN0: No regional lymph node metastasis.  pN0: No positive regional nodes.  M0: No distant metastasis.  Gleason 7: Moderately differentiated (moderate anaplasia).  Gleason Equal or Less than 6: Well differentiated (slight anaplasia).  Gleason equal or more than 8: Poorly differentiated/undifferentiated (marked anaplasia).  (AJCC 7th ed.)

label.value: Stage III Prostate Cancer AJCC v7

value.value: Stage III includes: T3a-b, N0, M0, Any PSA, Any Gleason.  cT3a: Tumor with extracapsular extension (unilateral or bilateral).  pT3a: Tumor with extraprostatic extension or microscopic invasion of bladder neck.  T3b: Tumor invades seminal vesicle(s).  cN0: No regional lymph node metastasis.  pN0: No positive regional nodes.  M0: No distant metastasis.  (AJCC 7th ed.)

label.value: Stage IV Prostate Cancer AJCC v7

value.value: Stage IV includes: (T4, N0, M0, Any PSA, Any Gleason); (Any T, N1, M0, Any PSA, Any Gleason); (Any T, Any N, M1, Any PSA, Any Gleason). cT4: Tumor is fixed or invades adjacent structures other than seminal vesicles such as external sphincter, rectum, bladder, levator muscles, and/or pelvic wall.  pT4: Invasion of rectum, levator muscles, and/or pelvic wall.  N1: Metastasis in regional lymph node(s).  M1: Distant metastasis.  (AJCC 7th ed.)

label.value: Testicular Cancer TNM Finding v7

value.value: A finding about one or more characteristics of testicular cancer, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system.

label.value: Testicular Cancer Pathologic TNM Finding v7

value.value: A pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of testicular cancer, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system.  Histologic examination of the orchiectomy specimen must be used for the pathologic examination.  (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Testicular Cancer Pathologic Primary Tumor TNM Finding v7

value.value: A pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of testicular cancer, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system as they pertain to staging of the primary tumor.  The extent of primary tumor is usually classified after radical orchiectomy, and for this reason, a pathologic stage is assigned.  (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Testicular Cancer pTX TNM Finding v7

value.value: Testicular cancer in which the primary tumor cannot be assessed. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Erythema Multiforme Minor

value.value: Self-limiting form of erythema multiforme.

label.value: Testicular Cancer pT0 TNM Finding v7

value.value: No evidence of primary tumor (e.g., histologic scar in testis). (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Testicular Cancer pTis TNM Finding v7

value.value: Intratubular germ cell neoplasia (carcinoma in situ). (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Testicular Cancer pT1 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Testicular cancer with tumor limited to the testis and epididymis without vascular/lymphatic invasion; tumor may invade into the tunica albuginea but not the tunica vaginalis. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Testicular Cancer pT2 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Testicular cancer with tumor limited to the testis and epididymis with vascular/lymphatic invasion, or tumor extending through the tunica albuginea with involvement of the tunica vaginalis. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Testicular Cancer pT3 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Testicular cancer with tumor invading the spermatic cord with or without vascular/lymphatic invasion. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Testicular Cancer pT4 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Testicular cancer with tumor invading the scrotum with or without vascular/lymphatic invasion. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Testicular Cancer Pathologic Regional Lymph Nodes TNM Finding v7

value.value: A pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of testicular cancer, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system as they pertain to staging of regional lymph nodes.  (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Testicular Cancer pNX TNM Finding v7

value.value: Testicular cancer in which regional lymph nodes cannot be assessed.  (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Testicular Cancer pN0 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Testicular cancer with no regional lymph node metastasis. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Testicular Cancer pN1 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Metastasis with a lymph node mass 2 cm or less in greatest dimension and less than or equal to five nodes positive, none more than 2 cm in greatest dimension. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Metastatic Melanoma

value.value: A melanoma that has spread from its primary site to another anatomic site.  Melanomas frequently metastasize to lymph nodes, liver, lungs, and brain.

label.value: Testicular Cancer pN2 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Metastasis with a lymph node mass more than 2 cm but not more than 5 cm in greatest dimension; or more than five nodes positive, none more than 5 cm; or evidence of extranodal extension of tumor. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Testicular Cancer pN3 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Metastasis with a lymph node mass more than 5 cm in greatest dimension. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: RNA Sequence

value.value: The sequence of nucleotide residues along an RNA chain.

label.value: Testicular Cancer Pathologic Distant Metastasis TNM Finding v7

value.value: A pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of testicular cancer, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system as they pertain to distant metastases.  There is no pathologic M0 for testicular cancer. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Testicular Cancer pM1 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Testicular cancer with distant metastasis. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Testicular Cancer pM1a TNM Finding v7

value.value: Testicular cancer with non-regional nodal or pulmonary metastasis. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Testicular Cancer pM1b TNM Finding v7

value.value: Testicular cancer with metastasis other than to non-regional lymph nodes and lung. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Testicular Cancer Clinical TNM Finding v7

value.value: A clinical finding about one or more characteristics of testicular cancer, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system.

label.value: Testicular Cancer Clinical Regional Lymph Nodes TNM Finding v7

value.value: A clinical finding about one or more characteristics of testicular cancer, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system as they pertain to staging of regional lymph nodes.  (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Testicular Cancer cNX TNM Finding v7

value.value: Testicular cancer in which the regional lymph nodes cannot be assessed.  (from AJCC 7th Ed.)
